cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.PL

Reasoning: The paper discusses a new language for writing objective functions over image- or graph-structured unknowns and optimizing them using GPU solvers. This is relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) as both fields involve processing visual data. The use of GPU solvers also suggests a focus on parallel computing (cs.DC) and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the language itself is a domain-specific language (cs.PL) designed for a specific problem domain.
